<p dir="ltr">However, fans shouldn't get their hopes up too soon. Black Ops 7 is revealed to be a co-op campaign, so it is possible the scene in question is just a section of the campaign used to show off four-player co-op. Additionally, known Call of Duty insider "The Ghost of Hope" <a href="https://x.com/TheGhostOfHope/status/1931779343421677956" rel="nofollow ">claims the Avalon map was scrapped</a> for battle royale and would be used for campaign and Outbreak Zombies mode for Black Ops 7.</p><p dir="ltr">Of course, we'll likely learn more about Black Ops 7 and Warzone in the coming weeks, as Activision says more details will be revealed later this summer.</p><p dir="ltr">Season 4 is currently live in Black Ops 6 and Warzone. The season features a crossover event with the Ballerina movie, which is part of the John Wick universe. Players can earn free cosmetics and unlock a new marksman rifle during the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/cod-black-ops-6-and-warzone-how-to-unlock-essex-model-07-and-all-ballerina-event-rewards/2900-6642/#2">Ballerina event in Black Ops 6 and Warzone</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
